-- Shanghai Ranked Most Likely to Join New York-Topped Financial Center List
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-08T02:13:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/shanghai-ranked-most-likely-to-join-new-york-topped-financial-center-list.html

          
          
             New York topped a list of global
financial centers in a ranking announced by Xinhua News Agency
and CME Group Index Services LLC in Shanghai today.  
 London ranked second, followed by Tokyo and Hong Kong,
according to the Xinhua-Dow Jones International Financial
Centers Development Index.  
 Shanghai, which ranked eighth, was the most likely city to
become a financial center, according to a report containing the
ranking.    
